`,e.jsx(t.p,{children:"AgentOps RAG is a production-style retrieval platform for agentic applications. The point is not to prove that a model can answer questions from documents. The point is to show the infrastructure an engineering team needs before trusting retrieval in a multi-tenant product: tenant boundaries, async ingestion, replayable failures, grounded answers, evals, traces, rate limits, and benchmarks."}),`
`,e.jsx(t.p,{children:"The repo is intentionally explicit. It avoids hiding the runtime behind a large agent framework so the important system boundaries stay visible."}),`
`,e.jsx(d,{groups:[{title:"API boundary",items:["FastAPI","JWT tenant claims","endpoint rate limits"]},{title:"Data plane",items:["Redis Streams","Postgres metadata","OpenSearch BM25 + vector"]},{title:"Agent plane",items:["planner","retriever tool","coverage critic","finalizer"]}],caption:"The project separates request handling, ingestion/storage, and agent execution so each layer has a clear owner and failure model."}),`
