`,e.jsxs(t.p,{children:["The write path starts at ",e.jsx(t.code,{children:"POST /documents"}),". The API validates the JWT, derives tenant ID from claims, stores metadata in Postgres, and enqueues an ingestion job in Redis Streams. The worker chunks the document, indexes chunks into OpenSearch, updates document state, and writes failed jobs to a DLQ with tenant ID, document ID, stage, and retry count."]}),`
`,e.jsxs(t.p,{children:["The read path starts at ",e.jsx(t.code,{children:"POST /ask"}),". The endpoint applies tenant-scoped rate limits, runs the planner, executes tenant-filtered retrieval, sends retrieved evidence to the critic, and finalizes either a grounded answer or a refusal. Every answer includes a trace ID."]}),`
`,e.jsx(t.h2,{id:"design-decisions",children:e.jsx(t.a,{href:"#design-decisions",children:"Design decisions"})}),`
`,e.jsxs(t.p,{children:[e.jsx(t.strong,{children:"Tenant ID comes from JWT claims, not request bodies."})," This prevents a client from asking for another tenant by changing payload fields. The same rule applies to document listing, retrieval, and DLQ replay."]}),`
